\title{Torsion element}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-18}
\taxon{definition}

\p{Let #{R} be a ring, #{M} be an #{R}-module, let #{m\in M} be an element of #{M}. We say #{m} is \define{Torsion} if its annihilator is nonzero
##{\Annihilator_{R}(m)\neq0.}
Specifically, the annihilator contains a non-zero-divisor nonzero element.}
